  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1300 mg
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/bacon-cream-supreme-spaghetti-60196f9caad9ba2ec650ad97
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and
mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Toss broccoli on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @bacon{4%ounce} on empty side. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets;
roast bacon on top rack and broccoli on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until broccoli is tender and bacon is crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If bacon is done before broccoli, remove from sheet and continue roasting broccoli.

Once bacon is cool enough to handle, chop into bite-size pieces.

While broccoli and bacon roast, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot of boiling water.
Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 1/2 cups pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Once broccoli and bacon are done, melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in pot used
for pasta over medium heat; add garlic and cook until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}.

Add @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce} and 1 cup reserved pasta cooking water
(1 1/2 cups for 4 servings); whisk to combine. Cook, whisking, until slightly
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} to combine.

Add drained spaghetti, 1 TBSP butter, and half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup} (save
the rest for serving) to pot with sauce. Cook, tossing, until pasta is coated in
a creamy sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}. (TIP: If necessary, stir in more reserved pasta
cooking water a splash at a time.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Stir bacon and broccoli into pasta, then divide between plates. Sprinkle with
remaining Parmesan and serve.